closure_reason: Case Closed. Closed date : 2021-05-05 16:16:16.26 Case Resolved This is related to commercial trash pickups.  Unfortunately  there is not much that the APCC can do about commercial trash pickups.  The City of Boston cannot restrict trash pickup hours in areas that are designated as commercial zones. The Commonwealth of Massachusetts does not give municipalities authority to restrict commercial trash pickup hours. (See Below)  (Massachusetts General Laws Title XVI  Chapter 111  Section 31A):     ....no rules or regulations shall restrict the hours of the day when garbage  offal or other offensive substances may be collected in areas zoned for business  commercial or industrial use.  Please let constituents know about that when they are logging a complaint regarding a business (commercial) trash pickup.  The APCC would appreciate that.  Thank you!  Lugardy Raymond
subject: Neighborhood Services
